Enum AnnotatedPluginDocument.ActiveLinkSaveBehaviour

  • java.lang.Object

    AnnotatedPluginDocument

    public static enum AnnotatedPluginDocument.ActiveLinkSaveBehaviour
extends Enum<AnnotatedPluginDocument.ActiveLinkSaveBehaviour>
    Gives an action to take when AnnotatedPluginDocument.saveDocument(com.biomatters.geneious.publicapi.documents.AnnotatedPluginDocument.ActiveLinkSaveBehaviour, jebl.util.ProgressListener) is called. Only applicable when the document has at least one descendant operation with active links.
    Since:
    API 4.60 (Geneious 5.6.0)

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant and Description
      DeactivateLinks
      For the parent and for every immediate descendant operation with active links, will automatically deactivate the link.
      DoNotPropagateChangesButKeepActive
      Keep any active links to descendant operations active, but do not propagate changes.
      PromptUser
      Prompt the user for which of the other behaviours (PropagateChanges, DeactivateLinks) to do.
      PropagateChanges
      For every descendant operation with active links, will recursively recompute all that operation's descendants automatically.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • PropagateChanges

        public static final AnnotatedPluginDocument.ActiveLinkSaveBehaviour PropagateChanges
        For every descendant operation with active links, will recursively recompute all that operation's descendants automatically. If this document is actively linked to the parent, the link will be maintained as an active link.

      • DoNotPropagateChangesButKeepActive

        public static final AnnotatedPluginDocument.ActiveLinkSaveBehaviour DoNotPropagateChangesButKeepActive
        Keep any active links to descendant operations active, but do not propagate changes. This should only be used for example when making changes to a document that won't have any effect on descendant documents and whose changes may be freely discarded if this document is regenerated from its parent document.

      • DeactivateLinks

        public static final AnnotatedPluginDocument.ActiveLinkSaveBehaviour DeactivateLinks
        For the parent and for every immediate descendant operation with active links, will automatically deactivate the link.

      • PromptUser

        public static final AnnotatedPluginDocument.ActiveLinkSaveBehaviour PromptUser
        Prompt the user for which of the other behaviours (PropagateChanges, DeactivateLinks) to do. This dialog will not be cancellable. Instead where possible, viewers or operations that modify documents should handle prompting the user at an earlier stage. This is also preferable if the user edits many documents at once to provide a single dialog. If the document is actively linked to its parent the user will be notified and the parent link deactivated. On Geneious Server, this option is equivalent to PropagateChanges for descendant links and DeactivateLinks for parent links.
